# Changes
## Mob Variants
- Cluckshroom chicken variant now drops Red Mushroom instead of Raw Chicken
- Swamp zombie nautilus variant now drops Lily Pads instead of Rotten Flesh
- Cold zombie nautilus variant now drops Packed Ice instead of Rotten Flesh
- Guardian zombie nautilus variant now drops Prismarine Crystals instead of Rotten Flesh
- Husk zombie nautilus variant now drops Sand instead of Rotten Flesh
- Creaking wolf variant now drops Resin Clumps
- Added Turkey chicken variant (spawns in Taiga biomes)
- Added Legend pig variant (spawns in Pen structures)
- Added Glow zombie nautilus variant:
    - Has a chance to spawn during full moon and in Lush/Dripstone Caves
    - When fully submerged in water it starts glowing
    - Drops Glow Ink Sacs on death
- Added Slime wolf and cat variants:
    - Does not spawn naturally anywhere
    - Can only be obtained by giving a tamed cat or wolf a Gooey Treat Item
    - Bounces a lot
    - Drops Slime when killed
- Skeleton variants for Cats and Wolves now also use Skeleton sounds
- Added Container Sulfur Cube Archetype. It's as heavy as the High Resistance Archetype but floats on water. Is applied by giving it a Shulker Box (Contents remain in the Shulker Box)
- Added Balloon Sulfur Cube Archetype. Is applied by giving it a Glass Block. Starts floating, gets a random size and turns invisible when it's leashed

## Structures
- Added Slime Dungeon Structures (Generates in the same biomes underground as the Trial Chamber does)
- Updated structure sets to distribute Nice Mob Variants structures better

## Items/Blocks
- Added Gooey Treat Item (Can be obtained from Trial Spawner in Slime Dungeon Structures)
- Chorus Flowers & Chorus Plants are now placeable on Farmland, Dirt, Grass, Mud, Moss & Podzol Blocks
- Podzol now supports vegetation
- Cocoa Beans can now be placed onto every Log type
- Small Dripleaves are now placeable on Grass, Mud, Moss & Podzol Blocks
- Crafting Brown Dye from Orange and Black Dye now gives 2 Items in return
- Crafting Green Dye from Blue and Yellow Dye now gives 2 Items in return
- Added Totem of Homecoming item:
    - Can be crafted from 3 Echo Shards and 2 Amethyst Shards
    - Saves a player from dying much like a Totem of Undying
    - When previously used on a Waypoint Hub (Access needed) any Totem of Homecoming item will teleport a player to it when the Totem was used
    - After Teleporting the saved Waypoint Hub will be forgotten

## Enchantments
- Increased probability of getting Enchanted Books in loot of Rise structure
- Projectiles shot by a Crossbow with Flare enchantment now also explode after 1-5 seconds (increases with level (lvl 1 = 1 sec)) when no entity/block was hit before
- Projectiles shot by a Crossbow with Flare enchantment now get removed when they explode
- Added Velocity enchantment (doubles speed of shot projectiles. Can be obtained in enchanting tables and on random loot)
- Added Incognito enchantment (hides the wearers name tag. Can be obtained by trading books and on random loot)
- Added Bounce enchantment (lets the wearer bounce all over the place. Can be obtained in enchanting tables and on random loot)
- Removed trigger for chat messages from the ingame wiki with links to our new wiki (Entries on the wiki will be created by me over time)
- Removed Poppy Peace and Sting enchantments due to changes of how Entity Anger works
- Removed Lupine Echo and Thousand Sting Enchanted Scrolls/Enchantments due to entity anger changes

## Misc
- Changed server Links in the Custom Options of the pause menu to now show links to the servers wiki entry, homepage, world map and seed map
- Added option to Fabled Roots pause menu options to allow players to change how they trigger their race ability (Crouch, Sprint, Jump, Disabled)
- Added option to Fabled Roots pause menu options for players to get an info chat message about their current race & class
- Doubled the amount of death messages per race
- Performance improvements for the coordinate hud
- Villagers can follow players holding Emeralds again

# Fixes
- Lily Pad loot drops for chicken duck variants being able to get smelted
- Fixed Black wolf variant using the "angry" textures when they should use the "tame" ones
- Miner class getting Hermit Starter Equipment
- Small Dripleaves couldnt be placed no longer on Dirt & Farmland blocks due to tag list name change
- Fixed a typo in Pufferfish enchantment description
- Some bee heads not dropping due to anger changes
- Villagers flicking up in the air sometimes when they follow a player holding an emerald